Well, here's a story someone from the last thread said to upload again.

>you're a tired mercenary, walking alone through a barren land.
>Suddenly come across a wagon in the middle of nowhere, with oxen grazing what little grass is left.
>You enter and are immediately assaulted by the exotic smell of inceses.
>Then by the colorful tapestry.
>And then by the chiming bell you just activated.
>A graspy, low voice comes from a curtain.
>"Greetings, traveller, are you tired?"
>Out from the curtain comes an eyeless sphinx cat anthro
>From the dress, you expect it's a female
>She stops to hear any response
>You say "yeah"
>That fleshy skull seems to look happy, and goes to take a box and a pitcher
>She seems to have the whole place memorized
>While she puts the water to boil, she sits back at a table with two chairs
>You decide to sit on the other
>She heard it, and now asks if you want to play a game while the water boils.
>"It's called tarot, It will divine your future"
>She seems excited to explain it to you, and you seem excited to learn more.
>She waves her hands around the table, until reaching a small wooden box.
>Inside there are a bunch of cards.
>She starts to shuffle them.
>"I'll take one card, and it will say an aspect of your near future"
>She stops at one card, flips it to make the painted face visible, and touches some spots.
>Braille, makes sense
>"Ahh, an ace of cups, all kinds of abundance may be on your way
>I've noticed something divine influencing you"
>You ask what kind of abundance.
>"Oh any kind!
>Wealth...
>Glory..."
>Silence
>"Or love."
>The water is ready now, so she takes the pitcher and makes two cups of tea.
>Once you sip yours, you feel all the different kinds of spices she must know about.
>You feel relaxed.
(1/2)
